The paper deals with the construction of deterministic sensing matrices that satisfy a statistical isometry property, which is a topic in both information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The focus on expected performance rather than worst-case analysis suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) perspective. The use of group theory in the construction of the sensing matrices suggests a potential connection to matrix multiplication (cs.MM). Finally, the mention of sub-linear complexity suggests a numerical analysis (cs.NA) perspective.
